issue.body:
A quick review of some of our customization traits:

```
pub trait CryptoProvider: Send + Sync + Debug + 'static {
pub trait KeyLog: Send + Sync {
pub trait ClientSessionStore: Send + Sync {
pub trait Signer: Send + Sync {
pub trait ResolvesServerCert: Send + Sync {
```

Our newest customization trait (CryptoProvider) has a Debug bound, which is great. Most of our others don't.

That means some of our internal structs, like ServerConfig, implement a custom Debug that doesn't mention these traits:

https://github.com/rustls/rustls/blob/829471689e6c414b1bc2d51aef541d2ed1a31335/rustls/src/server/server_conn.rs#L340

Implementing a custom Debug isn't by itself a problem; we also do that in places to hide data that shouldn't wind up in logs. But when print the Debug format of a server config, for instance, it would be useful to know the type of the `CryptoProvider`, `KeyLog`, etc.

Since we have a breaking change coming up, it might be a useful time to add Debug bounds on these. The idea being that most implementations would implement something very simple, like the name of the implementing type. For instance, right now `struct Ring;` has `#[derive(Debug)]` so it just prints `Ring`.

